WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.000
Navigate to the 'Scout' tab using the top navbar.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:07.000
There are three main panels. The top right container is the playlist data.  

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:10.000
the top left container is the video player and match reports.

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:18.000
Use the buttons in container headers to expand or minimise their size. 

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:25.000
The tab panels on the left hand side of container headers can be used to move between the nested tab panels within containers.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:31.000
The video player control tools at the bottom of the tab can be used to view multiple camera angles, 

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.000
jump backward or forward, play, pause or seek on the timeline 

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:40.000
play the camera angle in picture-in-picture mode watch footage in an extended display

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:51.000
control the playback speed of the video,

00:00:52.000 --> 00:01:10.000
and create clips from the current video time that can be added to the draft playlist.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:18.000
The bottom container includes the timeline and rowwise event data in seperate tabs.

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Double-click on the buttons in the timeline to search on the video.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:37.000
Pause the video and click on a timeline button while holding 'command' to select and add to a draft playlist.

00:01:39.000 --> 00:01:44.000
You can also create playlists using the rowwise data in the other tab panels.

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:53.000
Use the table headers to filter tables and select data using the check boxes to create a new draft playlist or add selected rows to an existing draft playlist.

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:59.000
The draft playlist can then be saved, used to search events on the video, or to export clips as an .mp4 file
